{
  format: 1
  name: decimal-division-canonical-scale-unspecified
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#expressions", "§A.6", "§A.1", "§7.5"]
  tags: ["boundary"]
  note: "Spec gap. Annex A.6 requires division to select 'a result scale that provides at least sixteen significant fractional digits when available and never less than either operand's display scale', bounded by unstated 'implementation limits'; Annex A.1 requires a 'canonical sign and trailing-zero form' without defining which trailing-zero form is canonical. For 10 / 4 the exact value is 2.5, but the observable wire text could be '2.5' or '2.5000000000000000' (PostgreSQL numeric emits the latter) — the spec does not pin one. The same gap affects every avg() result (§7.5). The value comparison, not the call success, is what cannot be asserted."

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.decscale@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      a: "decimal"
      b: "decimal"
      $mut: {
        read: "return .a / .b"
      }
      $public: {
        math: {
          $mut: { read: ".read" }
        }
      }
    }
    $data: {
      a: "10"
      b: "4"
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { call: "public.math.read", args: {},
      expect: { outcome: unspecified } }
  ]
}
